Concept List
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NSURLComponents 
  — assists with the building URLs (with safe ASCII characters) from their individual components

NSURLQueryItem
  — represents a single name/value pair in the query portion of a URL

Scheme
  — the part of the URL that specifies the protocol to be used

Hostname (Host)
  — the name of the server where your request is destined (colloquially referred to as the “website name”)

Path
  — the portion of the URL that specifies the location for the resource you are requested

Query
  — the portion of the URL consisting of name/value pairs which are processed by the server when creating a response
